The Police Ministry said it's disgusted by the violence of protesting farmers in the Free State. Courtesy of #DStv403 SENEKAL - The Police Ministry said it's disgusted by the violence of protesting farmers. Free State Police are investigating a case of damage to property and public violence after clashes erupted outside a Senekal court. READ: Police van torched in Free State farm murder protest Farmers demanded that two suspects in the murder of farm manager Brendin Horner be released to them. Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development Minister Thoko Didiza has also condemned the violence by protesting farmers outside the court.